The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and neurobiological models for multi-task learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of factorized representations and nonparametric, memory-based approaches suggests that it could be in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The discussion of spatial coding in the hippocampus suggests that it could also be in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the mention of trajectory-dependent place cells suggests that it could be in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often deals with spatial representations.
